Rating: 4
I made this for a Girl's Nite party and everyone loved it. I agree with others that the caramel sauce and crust were exceptional. Be careful to watch the caramel closely, and don't let it boil too hard. I used Bryers peach ice cream and thought the flavor was a delicious compliment to the pecans and crust. I will DEFINATELY make again!

Rating: 4
Great summer dessert! I used fresh peach slices alternating with whole pecan halves to adorn the top of the pie. Yes, the crust was super!

Rating: 3
The caramel sauce was fantastic and easy to make! I received rave reviews about the crust, although be careful about it being too thick in the corners, where the bottom of pan and sides meet. It can be a tad hard to get through with the spoon, although still crumbly and delicious to eat. The peach was definitely noticeable (I used breyers Peach ice cream). However, that was the part I could do without. In the future, I think a coffee or mocha fudge ice cream would put this pie over the top. I will make it again soon, but with that one change.

Rating: 4
Everyone loved this. It was very easy, delicious, and made a beautiful presentation. I made it for my in-laws and they just loved it. The crust was out of this world. I used the leftover homemade caramel sauce for dipping sliced granny smith apples and also to add to my morning coffee. Yum!

